    "To model the multi-turn setting, we view the conversation as a Markov decision process (MDP), defined by a tuple (S, A, P, P 0, R, γ) where S is the state space, A is the action space, P is the transition kernel, P 0 is the initial state distribution, R is the reward function, and γ < 1 is the discount factor.",
